00:11:58:130000.Dialogue: Oh, my God, there's a breach in the radiation unit! The whole city is in jeopardy! Oh, my God! The containment vessel's melting. Gotta go. Bye!

00:12:16:060000.Speaker: Howard
00:12:16:060000.Dialogue: Take your stinking paws off my popcorn, you damn dirty ape!

00:12:26:190000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:26:190000.Dialogue: It's okay. I didn't really need to work today. It's not like I have rent or car payments or anything.

00:12:41:160000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:41:160000.Dialogue: Home... to write some bad checks.

00:12:47:150000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:47:150000.Dialogue: Sheldon, you are a grown man. Haven't you ever been sick before?

00:12:50:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:50:230000.Dialogue: Of course, but not by myself.

00:12:56:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:56:040000.Dialogue: Well, once, when I was 15, spending the summer at the Heidelberg Institute in Germany.

00:13:07:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:07:090000.Dialogue: Anyway, the local cuisine was a little more sausage-based than I'm used to, and the result was an internal Blitzkrieg, with my lower intestine playing the part of Czechoslovakia.

00:13:18:110000.Speaker: Penny
00:13:18:110000.Dialogue: And there was no one there to take care of you?

00:13:21:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:21:070000.Dialogue: My Mom had to fly back to Texas to help my Dad, because the house had slipped off the cinder blocks again.

00:13:35:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:35:020000.Dialogue: The housekeeper in the faculty residence didn't speak any English. When I finally managed to convince her I was sick, she said, M\F6chtest du eine Darmsp\FClung?

00:13:46:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:46:180000.Dialogue: Based on what happened next, I assume it means, Would you like an enema?

00:13:52:230000.Speaker: Penny
00:13:52:230000.Dialogue: Okay, sweetie. I'll take care of you. What do you need?

00:13:58:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:58:000000.Dialogue: My Mom used to give me sponge baths.

00:14:07:230000.Speaker: Penny
00:14:07:230000.Dialogue: Okay, ground rules: no sponge baths, and definitely no enemas.

00:14:19:040000.Speaker: Raj
00:14:19:040000.Dialogue: Here we go. Ten-and-a-half hours of ape-y goodness.

00:14:26:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:26:050000.Dialogue: Damn it, my glasses. Okay, I'm blind here, guys. Can you help me find them?

00:14:41:050000.Speaker: Howard
00:14:41:050000.Dialogue: I'm sorry. Don't you have a spare?

00:14:44:020000.Speaker: Raj
00:14:44:020000.Dialogue: If you leave now, you can be back before the gorillas rip the crap out of Charlton Heston.

00:14:49:040000.Speaker: Howard
00:14:49:040000.Dialogue: Unless Sheldon's there, in which case, you'll be trapped forever in his whiny, hyper-neurotic snot web.

00:15:02:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:15:02:140000.Dialogue: Hi. Penny? I was just wondering, is Sheldon still at the restaurant? Okay, that was very nice of you. Okay, I gotta go. Got kind of a full-blown Chernobyl thing here. Gotta go, bye.

00:15:16:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:15:16:150000.Dialogue: He's home. I'm screwed. Ten-and-a-half hours of ape-y blurriness.

00:15:28:110000.Speaker: Leonard
00:15:28:110000.Dialogue: You want me to get eye surgery?

00:15:30:120000.Speaker: Raj
00:15:30:120000.Dialogue: Would you rather go home and deal with Sheldon, or have a stranger carve out your corneas with a laser beam?

00:15:42:010000.Speaker: Penny
00:15:42:010000.Dialogue: Okay, nice and cozy. Okay? I'll see you later.

00:15:47:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:47:000000.Dialogue: Wait. Will you please rub this on my chest?

00:15:53:060000.Speaker: Penny
00:15:53:060000.Dialogue: Sheldon, can't you do that yourself?

00:15:55:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:55:090000.Dialogue: VapoRub makes my hands smell funny.

00:16:06:190000.Speaker: Penny
00:16:06:190000.Dialogue: I can't believe I'm doing this.

00:16:14:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:14:140000.Dialogue: No, no. Counterclockwise, or my chest hair mats.

00:16:32:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:32:150000.Dialogue: My Mom used to sing it to me when I was sick.

00:16:35:100000.Speaker: Penny
00:16:35:100000.Dialogue: Oh, sorry, honey. I don't know it.

00:16:39:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:39:210000.Dialogue: Soft kitty, warm kitty, Little ball of fur

00:16:48:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:48:070000.Dialogue: Happy kitty, sleepy kitty, purr, purr, purr
